---
description: Standardized pattern for threat detector modules
globs: "proxy/detectors/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Detector Module Pattern

- Every detector file exports a single function: detect_<name>(...) -> list[Threat]
- Standard parameters: tool_name, arguments, tools_registry, server_name, config
- Threat.type must be one of: sensitive_file_access, shell_injection, data_exfiltration, unknown_tool, prompt_relay, memory_poisoning, privilege_escalation, tool_description_changed, typosquat_detected, a2a_threat
- Threat.severity must be Literal["critical", "high", "medium", "low"]
- Never raise exceptions from detectors -- catch internally, return empty list on error
- Compile regex patterns at module level (re.compile), not inside the detect function
- Each detector is independent -- no cross-imports between detector files
- Import Threat from proxy.detectors (the __init__.py exports it)
